Text: what are side effects of birth control pills

Text: how long do birth control pills last
Message JSON: {"userId":"8d642f54-7c2f-4dd3-9b2d-98c5ca58a93e","text":"how long do birth control pills last"}

Text: The pill is a type of birth control that you take once a day, every day, at the same time. Most of them work to prevent ovulation (when your body releases an egg) - no egg, no baby! There are a ton of different kinds of birth control pills out there so if one doesn’t work for you, you have options.

Text: how does an internal condom work

A female condom (aka internal condom) is a pouch that you insert into your vagina to block sperm. It kinda looks like a big, floppy condom. And just like a condom, you need to use it every time you have sex. If you use a female condom, make sure you DON'T use a male condom.
